CMOverviewHelp

"<html>
<head>
<title>Overview of Code Medic</title>
</head>

Code Medic is a graphical front-end for various debuggers:  gdb, xdebug, Java.  It was designed to work with <a href=http://www.newplanetsoftware.com/jcc/>Code Crusader</a> but can also be used alone. 

<p>
See the <a href=jxhelp:CMGettingStartedHelp>getting started</a> page for a quick guide to using Code Medic.

<p>
Code Medic currently provides the following features:

<ul>
<li> <a href=jxhelp:CMSourceWindowHelp>Source view</a> for setting breakpoints and stepping through code
<p>
<li> <a href=jxhelp:CMSourceWindowHelp#FileList>Files window</a> provides access to all source files used by the program being debugged.
<p>
<li> <a href=jxhelp:CMVarTreeHelp>Variables window</a> for examining the values of variables, the contents of structures and objects, and the elements of <a href=jxhelp:CMVarTreeHelp#Array1D>arrays</a>.
<p>
<li> <a href=jxhelp:CMThreadsHelp>Threads window</a> for switching between threads
<p>
<li> <a href=jxhelp:CMStackHelp>Stack Trace window</a> for examining the execution stack and switching between frames
<p>
<li> <a href=jxhelp:CMCommandDirHelp>Command line interface</a> to provide access to all the other features provided by <a href=http://www.gnu.org/software/gdb/documentation/>gdb</a>

</ul>
For more information about a particular feature, simply click on the underlined text. To search for a word or phrase, select \"Find...\" from the Search menu, enter the text, and then select \"Search all sections\" from the Search menu.
</html>"
